<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100215610468806></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100215610468806><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=2&mid=100215610468806>RE: New Rogue In the Making</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=2&mid=100215610468806#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=73658><span id=Sage>DavivMcD</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>224 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Oct 3rd 8:41 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>There's something wrong with the way Tallicus/Kanzer is calculating a stats rating for rogues. Rogues are first and foremost a melee class, obviously, but more specifically, an offensive damage dealing melee, although there are times when they get whacked at a little. So if you're determining how well a race fits a rogue, you either have to count all the melee stats (STR STA AGI DEX), or just the offensive ones (STR DEX). Sure stamina isn't that important for a rogue; but neither is agility. I've got sucky stats in both (95 STA and 115 AGI, ick) but I'm just fine when the mob decides my damage is more taunting than the warrior's. So, calculating it with just offensive stats, we find Dorfs up on top with 190, barbies close at 183, and halflings way behind at 170. Or using all 4 melee stats, we get barbies with 370, dorfs at 360, and halflings at 350. What's my point? I forgot....oh wait there it is. Barbies are the best in overall stats, while dorfs are your best bet for offensive stats and halflings just sit around at third place. So barbs are strong but big and ugly; halflings are sneaky and cunning but weak; dorfs are a perfect mix of small, sneaky and strong, AND they can see in the dark! As for Everfrost being a great zone to get from 1-20 or whatever in, I wouldn't be able to stand the boredom! Near Kaladim you've got tons of zones for all ranges of levels, all easily accessible by newbies without much help. So go for the dorf rogue! Oh yeah, in any test of stats, offensive or overall, starting position, general fun factor, etc... Dark elves pretty much come dead last, even below gnomes. DE rogues are pretty much for a challenging game, not for having a good character. If you wanna look as "cool" as one, just take the trip to LGuk to get a mask and don't put yourself through the agony of having every level a hell level. =P<br>&nbsp;<br>Daviv McD 28th Dwarf Rogue<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=13233" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=13233</a></td></tr>
