	   <tr><td colspan=2>Oh yeah, (read the other post first) I'd also like to add that Dwarves are the second best rogues IMO.&nbsp;&nbsp;Although their stats don't sum up to what the halflings do, they are like a miniature barbie because the stats are spread out the same (if not better).  They have 100 dex (coooool), 90 str (second best, cooooool), and 80 agi (pretty sniffy).  They are only 5 points under a barbie rogue when you sum up all the rogue stats and they are spread out very nicely (100 in the second most important stat, 90 in the most important stat, and 80 in the... other stat).  Also, a few reasons that some people prefer dwarves over barbies AND halflings, they have night vision (forgot what kind, think it's infra) and they have that very nice bonus of being tiny.  Barbies can't go into some places do to their size (although the funniest thing I've seen in my intire EQ experience was when I saw a barbie stuck in the Kelethin bank door, EVERYONE was pissed until a nice druid came and turned his bulky butt into a wolf).  They also have a nice starting zone.  A lot of people think that EF is to isolated (barbie newb zone) but I think it's the best because of the variety of creatures there and it's not to hard to get to Qeynos from there.  Whew, I was hoping that that was going to be a short post, sheesh, I need to stop rambling.<br>&nbsp;<br>"We are not hermits.&nbsp;&nbsp;We who would rather have a decaying corpse fighting at our side then to have you and your stench within a mile of us."  -Me on Necros...  there's a lot more but it's a sig.</td></tr>
