	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hehe, well hello to you to.&nbsp;&nbsp;I had to quit because I made him on my sis's account and it didn't click that when she moves away (She was visiting from Japan.  She's in the Army and she moved to Germany when she left.) that I can't play on her account anymore.  I am going to get my own account and start another guy.  Anyway, responding to your question:  IMO and stat wise Barbies (Barbarians) make the best rogues (that's what mine is going to be).  People say that they are only good when it comes to Str, but their other stats are superior also.  If you add up the 3 main rogue stats (str, dex, agi) they have the highest (halflings are tied with them at the top).  Also, a lot of rogues prefer high sta and barbies have the best rogue sta in the game.  The 2 most important stats to a rogue are str and dex.  I say that str is more important (barbies stomp any compitition in that area with a 103 while the closest competitor is the dwarf with 90) but some say that dex is more important (the lowest rogue stat on a barbie at 80 but that's what the 30 extras are for).  Halflings are the most popular rogues and are comstantly argued to be the best.  If you add up the Halfling's rogue stats (the three I mentioned) you come up with a sum of 275 while the barbarian's comes up to 275 also.  The halfling's stats are:  str 70 (...HAHA!) agi 105 (dats pretty nice, but barbies are 92 agi and agi is the least important rogue stat) and their dex is 100 (cooool, but still, second most important stat and those 30 points are nice).  Since the sums are the same, they're equal, right?  No, because barbies are more spread out with a little spice stuck into the most important stat, str (com'on, rogues are for dmg dealing so str is essential, halflings are waaaay down there with 70 str, the 2nd lowest).  When I made my gnm rogue, I wasn't aware of how it was going to effect the rest of my short gnome life.  I was happy to get a 50 point BS with a 10 dmg weapon.  I thought I was bad sh*t, but then I went into an arena with a barbie rogue and he nailed me for 100 something then I relized just how much more bad as* I would be if I started as a barbie.  Barbies don't have any night vision, true, but any magical item can fix that.  Also, a lantern at low lvls deals with this (or if you are of true rogue spirit, you'll just crank up the gamma in options :p).  Anyway, I have so many opinions on how barbies out do any other rogue race and I continue on forever (I'm almost there anyway) but I'll just stop here.  I'll be back at the end of Oct with a super twink barbie rogue.  Yes, me, the totally anti-twink opinionated bastard is going to twink :p.  See you in the arenas Taerras.<br>&nbsp;<br>"We are not hermits.&nbsp;&nbsp;We who would rather have a decaying corpse fighting at our side then to have you and your stench within a mile of us."  -Me on Necros...  there's a lot more but it's a sig.</td></tr>
